Demograph — data sources and attribution
=========================================

This project's own work (code, visualization, curated events, derived data)
is released into the public domain under CC0 1.0 (see LICENSE). The derived
datasets are computed from the upstream sources below. CC0 covers our
additions, but the upstream CC BY sources still ask to be attributed when you
reuse the derived data (data/processed/*.csv, web/data.js, web/regions.js) —
please credit:

Cliopatria — historical polity boundary polygons, 3400 BCE–2024 CE
  Seshat Global History Databank
  https://github.com/Seshat-Global-History-Databank/cliopatria
  License: CC BY 4.0

HYDE 3.2.1 — History Database of the Global Environment (gridded population)
  Klein Goldewijk, K., A. Beusen, J. Doelman and E. Stehfest (2017)
  DOI: 10.17026/dans-25g-gez3
  License: the DANS deposit is CC0; the release readme states CC BY 3.0.
  (HYDE 3.3+ switched to CC BY-NC-SA — this project deliberately uses 3.2.1.)

Natural Earth — admin-0 country polygons (region boundaries)
  https://www.naturalearthdata.com
  Public domain.

Wikidata — religion (P140) and language (P37/P2936) claims per polity
  https://www.wikidata.org
  License: CC0.

Inspiration / homage (not reproduced here):
  John B. Sparks, "The Histomap: Four Thousand Years of World History"
